
[1]instruction

   INSTRUC'TION, n. [L. instructio.]

   1. The act of teaching or informing the understanding in that of which
   it was before ignorant; information.

   2. Precepts conveying knowledge.

   Receive my instruction and not silver. Prov.8.

   3. Direction; order; command; mandate. The minister received
   instructions from his sovereign to demand a categorical answer.
